\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Leakage sanity audit. Test A trains on shuffled labels and evaluates on the original labels: under leakage, shuffling would leave AUPRC high; we observe collapse toward the positive-class prior ($\approx 0.10$). Test B forces row-level stochasticity via 80\% random row masking with seeds $\{42,7,2024\}$ and confirms \texttt  {random\_state} \emph  {does} produce variance under active randomness --- but less than $0.003$ AUPRC std, reflecting TraitGym's strong feature signal rather than a bug. Test C audits the chrom-LOO split.}}{22}{table.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:leakage_sanity}{{6}{22}{Leakage sanity audit. Test A trains on shuffled labels and evaluates on the original labels: under leakage, shuffling would leave AUPRC high; we observe collapse toward the positive-class prior ($\approx 0.10$). Test B forces row-level stochasticity via 80\% random row masking with seeds $\{42,7,2024\}$ and confirms \texttt {random\_state} \emph {does} produce variance under active randomness --- but less than $0.003$ AUPRC std, reflecting TraitGym's strong feature signal rather than a bug. Test C audits the chrom-LOO split}{table.6}{}}
